description: The caustic Adder. Damage from its poison bite is always lethal.
The venerable Alpha. Its courage emboldens the creatures that stand beside it.
Canine. Hooved. Reptilian. Feathered. Insectoid. The Amalgam is all.
The amorphous Amoeba. Its sigils are ever changing.
Ah, the diligent Ant. Its strength is proportionate to the size of its colony.
The Flying Ant. Its diligence is matched only by its grounded cousin.
The Regal Ant Queen. She births a new Ant once played.
The meddlesome Bat. A minor terror.
The industrious Beaver. When played it constructs Dams adjacent to it.
The inviolable Beehive. When it is attacked you will draw a Bee.
The dauntless Bloodhound. It leaps to oppose new creatures when they are played.
The reckless Wild Bull. Anything in its path is flung over its ponderous skull.
The watchful Bullfrog. It leaps in the way of attacking flyers.
The undying Cat. Sacrificing the poor beast does not kill it.
The unkillable Cockroach. It returns to your hand after dying.
The meager Coyote. But what did you expect for only four bones?
That infanticidal Cuckoo... It chokes up the board with the broken eggs of its victims.
That filthy feral hog... It becomes incensed when its chimes are struck.
The unrelenting Dire Wolf. Those lucky enough to survive its first attack may expect another...
The loyal Dire Wolf Pup. The bone it digs up will be the first of many to meet its teeth.
The flighty Elk. It moves after attacking.
The nascent Fawn. It quickly grows into an Elk.
Hm. The licentious Field Mice. You will draw a copy when they are played.
The uninspiring Geck. Perhaps you can find a use for it?
The apotheosized Goat. The truest offering. Sacrificing it grants three blood.
The monstrous Grizzly. Its form speaks enough of its efficacy.
The hellacious Hodag! Its ever-rising power does not fall after a battle.
Poor abandoned child. It does not die when sacrificed... but do you have the heart to try?
The adept Kingfisher. A slippery hunter.
The voracious Lammergeier. Its power scales in proportion to your Bones.
The underestimated Pelt Lice. An inescapable aspect of the fur trade.
The inevitable maggot. They will lurch forth from your hand when your creatures are killed.
The covetous Magpie. It can fetch any card in your deck.
The fervid Mantis. Its prying claws strike both to the left and right.
The holy Mantis God. A perfect incarnation of terror.
The delectable Mealworm. Does your mouth not water at the sight?
The omnipresent Mole. It burrows and emerges to block any landborn attacker.
The stalwart Mole Man. The ultimate defense.
The regal Moose. The creatures of the wild make way for it.
A largely unimpressive specimen.
The adamantine Mud Turtle. Its shell can stop any attack... once.
The resourceful Opossum. A small creature for a small price.
Ah, the elusive Otter. It submerges itself during my turn.
The eternal serpent. Death strengthens it [c:bR]forever[c:].
The prudent Pack Rat. Never doubt the utility of a well stocked pack.
The ornery Porcupine. Sharp quills await those who dare attack it.
The sadistic Pronghorn. Woe be to those that meet the end of its antlers.
The thieving Raccoon! It gathers the bones of my creatures for you.
The tragic Rat King. When their tangled bodies become corpses you will gain four bones.
The nefarious Rattler. A brittle creature... once past its monstrous fangs.
The conniving Raven. A blight upon the skies.
A nascent Raven. It is no less conniving in its incubation.
The bloodthirsty Red Hart. Its power grows as blood is spilled...
The underappreciated Ring Worm. Its value is not readily apparent...
The tyrannical Great White. The master of the deep.
The tenacious Skink. It moves over when attacked, leaving its tail behind.
The reviled Skunk. Its stench reduces the strength of the enemy.
The stalwart Snapper. A near impenetrable defense.
I have no words for this freak of nature.
The meek Sparrow. An inexpensive, if feeble, flying creature.
Hm. I don't recall making that one...
Did I do that?
I'm... Actually I'm not sure what that is.
Ha! The wimpish Tadpole. Its future as a Bullfrog is meager compensation.
This level of brutish strength needs no explanation...
The pernicious Vulture. A tyrant of the skies.
The bountiful Warren. It spawns a rabbit when it is played.
The proud Wolf. A vicious contender.
The young Wolf Cub. It grows into a Wolf after a single turn.
The relentless Wolverine. Its hunger only grows greater as it kills.
